---
// Problem Section Component
---

<section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-gray-800">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
      <!-- Content -->
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="inline-flex items-center px-4 py-2 bg-orange-500/20 text-orange-300 border border-orange-500/30 rounded-full text-sm font-medium">
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 mr-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
            </svg>
            The Problem
          </div>
          <h3 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-white leading-tight">
            What's Missing in Today's School System?
          </h3>
        </div>
        
        <div class="space-y-6 text-lg text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            In today's school system, what's missing is <strong class="text-white">hands-on exposure</strong> — 
            the kind that connects classroom learning to how things actually work in the real world.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            Students are already exploring multiple interests — coding, creating, designing, experimenting — 
            yet they rarely understand what really goes on <strong class="text-white">behind the scenes</strong>. 
            Why wait until college to figure that out?
          </p>
          
          <p>
            Even engineering graduates often spend years trying to understand what they truly want to do. 
            Not because they lack capability, but because there's no <strong class="text-white">flow of understanding</strong> 
            that links their learning to real-world application.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="bg-orange-500/20 border-l-4 border-orange-400 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
          <p class="text-orange-300 font-medium">
            Many end up stuck in a loop of endless learning, without clarity or direction.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Visual -->
      <div class="relative">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-700 to-gray-600 rounded-2xl p-8 h-96 flex items-center justify-center">
          <!-- Illustration placeholder -->
          <div class="text-center space-y-4">
            <div class="w-24 h-24 mx-auto bg-gray-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">
              <svg class="w-12 h-12 text-gray-400" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8.228 9c.549-1.165 2.03-2 3.772-2 2.21 0 4 1.343 4 3 0 1.4-1.278 2.575-3.006 2.907-.542.104-.994.54-.994 1.093m0 3h.01M21 12a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="text-gray-300 font-medium">Students asking "What should I do?"</p>
            <div class="flex justify-center space-x-2">
              <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-orange-400 rounded-full animate-bounce"></div>
              <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-orange-400 rounded-full animate-bounce" style="animation-delay: 0.1s"></div>
              <div class="w-2 h-2 bg-orange-400 rounded-full animate-bounce" style="animation-delay: 0.2s"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Floating elements -->
        <div class="absolute -top-4 -right-4 bg-gray-700 border border-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-lg p-4 ">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
            <div class="w-3 h-3 bg-red-400 rounded-full"></div>
            <span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-200">Confusion</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div class="absolute -bottom-4 -left-4 bg-gray-700 border border-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-lg p-4 ">
          <div class="flex items-center space-x-2">
            <div class="w-3 h-3 bg-yellow-400 rounded-full"></div>
            <span class="text-sm font-medium text-gray-200">Endless Learning</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- The Missing Layer Section -->
<section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-gray-900">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h3 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-6">
        Understanding the Learning Gap
      </h3>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-300 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        Enhance your educational experience with our comprehensive approach, 
        offering deeper insights and meaningful connections for modern learning needs.
      </p>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Card Layout Grid -->
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 h-auto lg:h-96">
      <!-- Large Feature Card (Left) -->
      <div class="lg:col-span-2 bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-400/15 to-green-500/20 rounded-2xl p-8 text-white relative overflow-hidden h-full">
        <!-- Gradient Background -->
       
        
        <!-- Background Pattern -->
        <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-20">
          <svg class="w-full h-full" viewBox="0 0 400 300" fill="none">
            <circle cx="350" cy="50" r="80" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.3"/>
            <circle cx="50" cy="250" r="60" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.2"/>
            <path d="M200 100L250 150L200 200L150 150Z" fill="currentColor" opacity="0.4"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        
        <div class="relative z-10 h-full flex flex-col justify-between">
          <div class="mb-6">
            <span class="inline-block px-3 py-1 bg-white/20 rounded-full text-sm font-medium mb-4">
              Bridging the Gap
            </span>
            <h4 class="text-2xl lg:text-3xl font-bold mb-4">
              Our knowledge inspires us to innovate continuously
            </h4>
            <p class="text-emerald-100 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              We connect the "what" and "how" of learning with the crucial "why" - 
              transforming curiosity into clarity and learning into understanding.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <button class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-3 bg-white/20 hover:bg-white/30 rounded-lg text-white font-medium transition-colors duration-200 self-start">
            Explore Our Approach
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 ml-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"/>
            </svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Right Column - 2x2 Grid -->
      <div class="grid grid-rows-2 gap-6 h-full">
        <!-- Top Right Card - Sky Blue -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-400/20 to-cyan-500/15 rounded-2xl p-6 text-white relative h-full flex flex-col justify-between">
          <div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-start mb-4">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm text-sky-100 mb-2">Deep Understanding Through</p>
                <h5 class="text-xl font-bold mb-2">Why-Based Learning</h5>
              </div>
              <svg class="w-6 h-6 opacity-60 flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sky-100 text-sm">
              Connecting knowledge to real-world purpose and meaning.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <!-- Bottom Right Card - Dark Gray -->
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-700 to-gray-800 rounded-2xl p-6 text-white relative h-full flex flex-col justify-between">
          <div>
            <h5 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3">Complete Learning Solutions</h5>
            <p class="text-gray-300 text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Comprehensive educational strategies that bridge theory with practical application, 
              ensuring students understand not just what and how, but why.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex justify-end mt-4">
          
              <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/>
              </svg>
      
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Bottom Section -->
    <div class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
      <!-- Left Card - Sky Blue -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-sky-500/15 to-cyan-600/20 rounded-2xl border border-sky-500/30 p-8 relative">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <div>
            <p class="text-sky-300 text-sm font-medium mb-2">Innovative Solutions Driving Educational</p>
            <h5 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white">Knowledge Integration</h5>
          </div>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-white" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3"/>
            </svg>
        </div>
        <p class="text-sky-200">
          Transforming traditional learning approaches by connecting classroom knowledge 
          to real-world applications and industry insights.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Right Card - Summary -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500/15 to-gray-600/20 rounded-2xl p-8 shadow-lg border border-gray-700 relative">
        <h5 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-400 via-orange-300 to-gray-200 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
          That "Why" Connects Knowledge to Purpose
        </h5>
        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          It transforms curiosity into clarity, and learning into understanding. 
          That's the gap we're bridging - creating meaningful connections between 
          what students learn and why it matters in the real world.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>